programme.desc: Eighty years after the Battle of Saipan, a collection of battlefield interviews with US soldiers has been uncovered. Their voices tell the story of one of the most brutal chapters of the war.

programme.title: Origami Magic
programme.desc: Origami is magic made from a single sheet of paper. We introduce two artists who create paper "animals." and our expert "Dr. Origami," will teach you how to make an easy origami craft.

programme.title: CAT ENCOUNTERS
programme.desc: Join animal photographer Iwago Mitsuaki as he meets cats around the world! Today: in Val D'Orcia in Italy and Nagasaki, Japan. On Kitty Trivia, we discover why cats like to ride on shoulders.

programme.title: Nun's Seasonal Calendar
programme.desc: In this episode, we learn about boshu and geshi, two dates from early summer. The chefs prepare ume plums and tea leaves and teach us how to make a pair of refreshing summer dishes.

programme.title: Hit the Road 5minutes
programme.desc: Let's see Japan by car! We'll be driving through Hiroshima Prefecture, with our goal being the famed Itsukushima Shrine. Along the way, we'll make a few stops off the beaten path that will amaze you!

programme.title: 2024 ELECTION JAPAN DECIDES
programme.desc: Japanese voters head to the polls on October 27 for the Lower House election. NHK WORLD-JAPAN will provide updates and analysis as the results come in.

programme.title: GLOBAL AGENDA
programme.desc: World discussion in depth. Global opinion leaders debate key issues facing our modern world, presenting solutions to help solve these concerns.

programme.title: 100 CAMERAS
programme.desc: 100 CAMERAS zooms in on the Pokemon World Championships hosted in Japan. Go behind the scenes and follow several players as they prepare for the tournament, then battle to become the very best.

programme.title: My Street Piano
programme.desc: Karuizawa is a popular summer getaway. A piano was set up in a public space for a limited period during autumn, and players from all walks of life stopped by to share their favorite melodies.

programme.title: Core Kyoto mini
programme.desc: Kyoto has many stores specializing in traditional snacks and treats, called Oyatsu. Some purveyors continue to use age-old ingredients and methods.

programme.title: DESIGN MUSEUM JAPAN
programme.desc: Hokkaido / Takeya Takayuki (model maker) Fishing boats in the herring industry-which thrived here until the 1950s-featured swirling decorations that made a big impression on Takeya, a Hokkaido native.

programme.title: RAMEN JAPAN 5min.
programme.desc: Ramen packed with seafood goodness, loved in bitter cold northern Japan for over 100 years. Try a bowl for yourself!

programme.title: 2024 ELECTION JAPAN DECIDES
programme.desc: Japanese voters head to the polls on October 27 for the Lower House election. NHK WORLD-JAPAN will provide updates and analysis as the results come in.

programme.title: Darwin's Amazing Animals
programme.desc: A natural history show that's a huge hit with families in Japan has gone global! The series explores the amazing and delightful stories of animals all around the world, including Japan.

programme.title: ANIME MANGA EXPLOSION
programme.desc: This episode features CloverWorks, the 2018 animation studio famed for stunning visuals and dramatic storytelling. Get an exclusive look at their latest film and learn how they train young animators.

programme.title: Time-lapse 3min.
programme.desc: NHK WORLD-JAPAN presents a variety of short programs focusing on Japan and Asia.

programme.title: Fit With the Doctor's Cyborg
programme.desc: Breaking is included as a new event in the 2024 Olympic Games. Come learn "Pro Tips" and "Improvement Points" that will help you bust a move!

programme.title: Story Land in Classical Japanese
programme.desc: This program presents masterpieces of classical Japanese literature in both their original forms and modern translations, with easy-to-understand imagery that conveys the worldview of ancient Japan.

programme.title: Japanology Plus mini
programme.desc: Japanology Plus explores Japanese life and culture. In this 5-minute digest, we look at bladed tools. Traditional techniques are used to make a range of state-of-the-art items.

programme.title: 2024 ELECTION JAPAN DECIDES
programme.desc: Japanese voters head to the polls on October 27 for the Lower House election. NHK WORLD-JAPAN will provide updates and analysis as the results come in.

programme.title: tiny desk concerts JAPAN
programme.desc: ROTH BART BARON, the globally acclaimed folk rock band helmed by Mifune Masaya, is based in Tokyo and Berlin and renowned for their distinct sound. The group brings a one-of-a-kind performance to tdcJ

programme.title: PythagoraSwitch mini
programme.desc: There are hidden rules and unique ways of thinking, we can discover in our daily lives. With anime, songs, exercises, and Pythagora tools, get ready for fun! This time "Pythagora Equipment Academy"...
